The paper deals with online matching problems, which are typically studied in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses hypergraphs, which are a topic in graph theory (cs.GT). Information theory (cs.IT) is mentioned in the context of the competitive ratio analysis. The paper also discusses the use of randomized algorithms and their analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses applications to Internet advertising reservation systems, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
